[latex]5 \%[/latex] neutral donor atoms/dopant atoms means [latex]95 \%[/latex] donor atoms are ionized. Concentration of electrons occupying the donor level is given as [latex]
n_{d}=\frac{N_{d}}{1+\frac{1}{g} \exp \left(\frac{E_{D}-E_{F}}{k T}\right)}
