Given, [latex]
E_{F}-E_{V}=0.35 \mathrm{eV} \quad \text { [Considering it is given at } 400 \mathrm{~K} \text { ] }
[/latex] Also,

[latex]V_{T_{1}}=K T_{1}=0.026 \mathrm{eV}[/latex] at [latex]T_{1}=300 \mathrm{~K}[/latex] [latex]\therefore[/latex]

[latex]\frac{V_{T_{1}}}{V_{T_{2}}}=\frac{T_{1}}{T_{2}} \Rightarrow V_{T_{2}}=\frac{T_{2}}{T_{1}} \times V_{T_{1}}[/latex] [latex]\therefore[/latex]

[latex]V_{T_{2}}=\frac{400}{300} \times 0.026[/latex] [latex]V_{T_{2}}=0.03466 \mathrm{eV}[/latex] at [latex]T_{2}=400 \mathrm{~K}[/latex] Now,

[latex]N_{v}=1 \times 10^{19} / \mathrm{cm}^{3}[/latex] at [latex]T_{1}=300 \mathrm{~K}[/latex] [latex]N_{v} \propto T^{3 / 2}[/latex] [latex]\frac{N_{V_{2}}}{N_{V_{1}}}=\left(\frac{T_{2}}{T_{1}}\right)^{3 / 2}[/latex] [latex]N_{V_{2}}=\left(\frac{T_{2}}{T_{1}}\right)^{3 / 2} N V_{1}[/latex] [latex]\left(\because T_{2}=400 \mathrm{~K}\right)[/latex]

[latex]=\left(\frac{400}{300}\right)^{3 / 2} N_{V_{1}}[/latex] [latex]N_{V_{2}}=1.5396 \times 10^{19} / \mathrm{cm}^{3}[/latex] Now, hole concentration at [latex]400 \mathrm{~K}[/latex] is given as [latex]
\begin{aligned}
& p=N_{V} e^{-\left(E_{F}-E_{V}\right) / k T_{2}}=1.5396 \times 10^{19} \times e^{-0.35 \mathrm{eV} / 0.03466 \mathrm{eV}} \\
& p=63.36 \times 10^{13} \mathrm{~cm}^{-3}
\end{aligned}
[/latex]

Given, intrinsic carrier concentration [latex]n_{i}=1 \times 10^{10} \mathrm{~cm}^{-3}[/latex] Hole concentration, [latex]\quad p=1.5 \times n_{i}[/latex] [latex]
p=1.5 \times 10^{10} \mathrm{~cm}^{-3}
[/latex] Given, electron and hole current are equal [latex]
\begin{aligned}
I_{p \text { dritt }} & =I_{n \text { dritt }} \\
p q \mu_{p} E A & =n q \mu_{n} E A \\
1.5 \times 10^{10} \mu_{p} & =n \mu_{n} \quad ...(i)
\end{aligned}
[/latex] But according to mass action law, [latex]
\begin{aligned}
n p & =n_{i}^{2} \\
n & =\frac{n_{i}}{1.5}=\frac{10^{10}}{1.5} \mathrm{~cm}^{-3}
\end{aligned}
[/latex] Put in equation (i) [latex]\therefore \quad 1.5 \times 10^{10} \mu_{p}=\frac{10^{10}}{1.5} \times \mu_{n}[/latex] [latex]
\frac{\mu_{n}}{\mu_{p}}=2.25
[/latex]

